                            <comment id="12831128" author="gdusbabek" created="Mon, 8 Feb 2010 21:27:59 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This fixes the problem, but I don&apos;t see the point of having Bootstrapper launch a separate thread to make the file requests while SS.init waits for bootstrapping to finish.  Its work could mostly be replaced with a method in SS that calls into the static methods currently in Bootstrapper.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12831132" author="jbellis" created="Mon, 8 Feb 2010 21:34:07 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1 on the patch.  I&apos;m not sure what the point of having the separate BS thread is, either.  Maybe it made more sense a dozen refactors ago. &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/smile.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
